ğŸ›¡ï¸ Security Groups:
Instance-Level: Controls inbound/outbound traffic to EC2 instances.
Stateful: Automatically allows response traffic.
Allow Rules Only: If it's not allowed, it's blocked by default.
Example: Allow HTTP traffic (port 80) to a web server, keeping other ports secure.

ğŸ”’ Network ACLs:
Subnet-Level: Manages traffic at the subnet level.
Stateless: Requires explicit rules for both inbound and outbound traffic.
Allow & Deny Rules: Provides more granular control.
Example: Block all but specific IP addresses from accessing a private subnet.
Together, they form a strong, multi-layered security setup. ğŸŒğŸ”

