How COVID-19 Pushed Blinkit to Cut AWS Costs by 50%

Before COVID, they were laser-focused on growth, using AWS as a core driver. However, the pandemic made them rethink their strategy and focus on efficiency to better serve their customers. Through strategic cost-cutting measures, they successfully reduced their AWS costs by 50%, saving millions annually ğŸ‘‡ğŸ» 

Key Areas of Optimization ğŸ” 
1ï¸âƒ£ Data Transfer Costs ğŸ‘‡ğŸ»
â¡ They identified significant costs from NAT Gateway and cross-AZ traffic.
â¡ Solution: Deployed VPC endpoints for S3, reducing data transfer costs by 30%.

2ï¸âƒ£ EC2 & Reserved InstancesğŸ‘‡ğŸ»
â¡ After right-sizing instances and leveraging Spot Instances, they cut EC2 costs by 40%.
â¡ Migrating workloads to Convertible RIs ensured 100% utilization, minimizing wastage.

3ï¸âƒ£ S3 Costs ğŸ‘‡ğŸ»
â¡Without proper lifecycle policies, S3 costs were steadily rising.
â¡ Implemented intelligent tiering and data compression for backups, leading to 25% cost savings.

4ï¸âƒ£ Resource Optimization ğŸ‘‡ğŸ»
â¡ By scaling down their stage environments at night and reducing unnecessary EBS volumes, they saved 35% on stage infrastructure.
â¡ Additionally, Pod resource requests were optimized, reducing Kubernetes CPU usage by 70%.

5ï¸âƒ£ Spot Instances ğŸ‘‡ğŸ»
â¡ Shifting to Spot Instances for 99% of production workloads drastically reduced EC2 costs. Managed spot coverage through autoscaling groups with graceful shutdown mechanisms to ensure availability.

Tools Used ğŸ› ï¸ 
â¡ AWS Cost Explorer: For identifying major cost contributors.
â¡ Athena & CUR: For granular insights on S3, EC2, and data transfer usage.
â¡ VPC Flow Logs: To identify traffic patterns and optimize data transfer.

Result âš¡
â¡ They successfully reduced AWS costs by 50%, with no impact on performance or availability, ensuring more savings during a challenging time.
â¡ This was a huge learning experience in efficiency, and they are continuing to optimize further!

